AWS Tools
AWS CodePipeline: CI/CD service automating build, test, and deploy phases.
AWS Secrets Manager: Manages and protects secrets such as API keys and passwords.
AWS Security Hub: Centralizes security alerts and compliance status across AWS accounts.
Amazon Inspector: Automated security assessment service for AWS applications.
AWS Config: Tracks and evaluates AWS resource configurations for compliance.

Azure Tools
Azure DevOps: Comprehensive CI/CD and agile planning service for development teams.
Azure Security Center: Unified security management and advanced threat protection for cloud workloads.
Azure Key Vault: Securely stores and manages secrets, keys, and certificates.
Azure Policy: Enforces organizational policies to ensure resource compliance.
Microsoft Defender for Cloud: Threat protection across Azure and hybrid environments.

Third-Party Tools
Code Quality and Security Analysis

SonarQube: Continuous code quality and security analysis tool.
Checkmarx: Static Application Security Testing (SAST) tool for identifying code vulnerabilities.
Dependency and Container Security

Snyk: Finds and fixes vulnerabilities in dependencies and container images.
Black Duck: Identifies open-source vulnerabilities and compliance issues.
Infrastructure as Code

Terraform (by HashiCorp): Infrastructure as Code tool for managing cloud resources.
Ansible: Automates configuration management, application deployment, and task automation.
Secret Management

HashiCorp Vault: Secures, stores, and tightly controls access to secrets and sensitive data.
Web Application Security Testing

OWASP ZAP (Zed Attack Proxy): Open-source web application security scanner.
Burp Suite: Web application security testing tool.
Vulnerability Scanning

Nessus: Vulnerability scanning tool for identifying security issues.
OpenVAS: Open-source vulnerability scanner for network and application security.
Monitoring and Logging

Prometheus & Grafana: Monitoring and alerting toolkit with customizable dashboards.
ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana): Centralized logging and real-time data visualization tools.
Splunk: Provides powerful log analysis and SIEM capabilities.
Container Security

Aqua Security: Provides security for containerized applications, including image scanning and runtime protection.
Twistlock: (Now part of Palo Alto Networks) Offers container and cloud-native security.
Clair: An open-source project for the static analysis of vulnerabilities in application containers.
Regression Testing

Selenium: Automates browsers for testing web applications.
JUnit: A widely used testing framework for Java programming.
TestNG: A testing framework inspired by JUnit, designed for testing in Java.
Penetration Testing

Metasploit: A penetration testing framework for finding and exploiting vulnerabilities.
Kali Linux: A Linux distribution with numerous tools for penetration testing and security research.
Kubernetes Tools

Kubernetes: An open-source system for automating deployment, scaling, and operations of application containers.
Helm: Package manager for Kubernetes applications, simplifies deployment and management.
Kube-bench: Checks Kubernetes clusters against common security best practices (CIS benchmarks).
Kubernetes Dashboard: A web-based Kubernetes user interface.
